WEBVTT

00:01.672 --> 00:03.044
PREVIOUSLY ON "REVENGE"...

00:03.044 --> 00:04.045
I KNOW ABOUT YOU AND BEN.
I HAVE ONE CERTAINTY IN MY LIFE.

00:04.045 --> 00:05.126
AND THAT IS
HOW I FEEL ABOUT YOU.

00:05.126 --> 00:07.628
I CAN'T, JACK.
I'M SORRY.

00:07.628 --> 00:08.889
IF YOU'RE GONNA KEEP
COMING AT ME,

00:08.889 --> 00:10.931
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO BE
A HELL OF A LOT SMARTER.

00:10.931 --> 00:13.134
I WILL FIND
YOUR WEAK SPOT.

00:13.134 --> 00:15.266
ARE YOU LOOKING
FOR MY EX-WIFE?
 I FOUND HER.

00:15.266 --> 00:16.557
AND IF YOU DON'T DO
AS I ASK,

00:16.557 --> 00:18.559
I COULD LET ANOTHER PERSON KNOW
WHO WANTS TO FIND HER

00:18.559 --> 00:20.351
FOR A COMPLETELY
DIFFERENT REASON.

00:20.351 --> 00:22.733
THE REMAINDER OF
EDWARD GRAYSON'S ESTATE

00:22.733 --> 00:24.195
IS BEING LEFT TO HIS WIFE.

00:24.195 --> 00:25.276
SO SORRY I'M LATE.

00:25.276 --> 00:27.148
TEDDY AND I WERE MARRIED
FOUR MONTHS AGO.

00:27.148 --> 00:28.909
THIS WILL IS FRAUDULENT.

00:28.909 --> 00:30.701
David: WHAT'S YOUR PLAN
FOR THAT KETCH?

00:30.701 --> 00:33.114
HOW ABOUT YOU BUY ME
A DRINK...AND IT'S YOURS?

00:33.114 --> 00:35.416
[ CHUCKLES ]
 YOUR CAMPAIGN IS SINKING.

00:35.416 --> 00:37.498
I ALWAYS FIND A WAY
TO COME OUT ON TOP.

00:37.498 --> 00:38.499
I UNDERSTAND
HOW IT FEELS

00:38.499 --> 00:40.040
TO BE SCREWED
OUT OF AN INHERITANCE.

00:40.040 --> 00:42.543
I NEED A LAWYER,
NOT AN OPPORTUNIST.

00:42.543 --> 00:44.044
WELL, IT'S A GOOD THING
FOR YOU THAT I'M BOTH.

00:46.127 --> 00:49.170
[ WHISTLE BLOWS ]

00:49.170 --> 00:50.341
WHAT THE HELL WAS THAT
IN THERE?

00:50.341 --> 00:52.513
ONE SOUR LOOK FROM THE JUDGE,
AND YOU FLEE?!

00:52.513 --> 00:54.135
YOU TOLD ME
THAT YOU WERE A PIT BULL,

00:54.135 --> 00:56.767
BUT YOU NEGLECTED TO MENTION
THAT YOU'VE BEEN NEUTERED.

00:56.767 --> 00:58.018
VICTORIA,
HE SAID IF ALL WE HAD

00:58.018 --> 00:59.730
WERE LIES AND CONJECTURE,
THERE'D BE SANCTIONS.

00:59.730 --> 01:02.233
WHICH IS WHY I'VE NOT ONLY LOST
MY RIGHTFUL INHERITANCE,

01:02.233 --> 01:03.023
BUT ALL RESPECT FOR YOU.

01:03.023 --> 01:04.894
I STILL HAVE A CAREER
TO CONSIDER.

01:04.894 --> 01:07.027
OH, NOT IN THIS PART
OF THE COUNTRY YOU DON'T.

01:07.027 --> 01:09.029
GO HOME, MR. ELLIS.

01:09.029 --> 01:10.741
THERE IS NOTHING LEFT
FOR YOU HERE --

01:10.741 --> 01:12.693
NO CAMPAIGN, NO CAREER,

01:12.693 --> 01:14.695
NOT EVEN THAT LITTLE SISTER
OF YOURS

01:14.695 --> 01:17.698
WILL GIVE YOU
THE TIME OF DAY.

01:19.750 --> 01:22.543
Natalie: WHERE'S YOUR
TOY ATTORNEY RUNNING OFF TO?

01:22.543 --> 01:25.045
[ CHUCKLES ]

01:25.045 --> 01:26.837
YOU MAY HAVE LOST
IN THERE --

01:26.837 --> 01:28.299
AND REMARKABLY QUICKLY,
I MIGHT ADD --

01:28.299 --> 01:30.421
BUT NO HARD FEELINGS.

01:30.421 --> 01:33.013
I WAS HOPING TO INVITE YOU
TO MY SHINDIG THIS WEEKEND.

01:33.013 --> 01:36.016
YOU'RE THROWING
THE ANNUAL FOURTH OF JULY PARTY?

01:36.016 --> 01:39.390
IT WAS A LAST-MINUTE DECISION,
AND THE DATE WAS OPEN SO...

01:39.390 --> 01:40.721
OH.

01:40.721 --> 01:42.022
OH, THIS MUST BE
HARD FOR YOU,

01:42.022 --> 01:44.525
CONSIDERING THIS PARTY'S
ALWAYS BEEN A GRAYSON TRADITION.

01:44.525 --> 01:47.488
WELL, IT STILL IS,
CONSIDERING THAT YOU'LL BE USING

01:47.488 --> 01:50.110
STOLEN GRAYSON MONEY
TO THROW IT.

01:50.110 --> 01:53.033
OR MAYBE YOU FOUND
ANOTHER SUITOR TO SWINDLE.

01:53.033 --> 01:54.995
SHOULD I CHECK
THE OBITUARIES?

01:54.995 --> 02:00.201
VICTORIA, LOOK, YOU GAVE IT
YOUR BEST SHOT IN COURT.

02:00.201 --> 02:01.662
IT'S OVER.

02:01.662 --> 02:03.624
YOU CLEARLY
DON'T KNOW ME.

02:03.624 --> 02:07.127
WHICH IS EXACTLY WHY
I WANT YOU TO COME TOMORROW.

02:07.127 --> 02:09.128
[ CHUCKLES ]

02:16.677 --> 02:19.890
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

02:19.890 --> 02:23.604
[ BELL RINGING IN DISTANCE ]

02:26.227 --> 02:27.608
DO YOU LIKE HER?

02:27.608 --> 02:30.481
DEPENDS ON WHAT "HER"
YOU'RE REFERRING TO.

02:30.481 --> 02:31.902
I HAVE TO HEAR
THROUGH THE GRAPEVINE

02:31.902 --> 02:33.984
THAT NOT ONLY
ARE YOU SEEING A GRAYSON,

02:33.984 --> 02:35.406
BUT YOU'RE ACCEPTING GIFTS
FROM HER, TOO?

02:35.406 --> 02:36.407
WHAT THE HELL, DAD?

02:36.407 --> 02:37.948
NO,
I-I DIDN'T SAY ANYTHING

02:37.948 --> 02:39.740
'CAUSE THERE'S NOT REALLY
MUCH TO SAY.

02:39.740 --> 02:41.912
NATALIE AND I HAD DRINKS
A COUPLE OF TIMES --

02:41.912 --> 02:44.044
DINNER TONIGHT,
AND THAT'S ABOUT IT.

02:44.044 --> 02:47.047
IF IT HELPS YOU AT ALL,
UH, SHE DESPISES VICTORIA.

02:47.047 --> 02:49.210
STILL A GRAYSON.

02:49.210 --> 02:50.921
SHE'S A GRAYSON,
BUT ONLY IN NAME.

02:50.921 --> 02:52.002
HEY, TRUST ME.

02:52.002 --> 02:53.844
I'VE BEEN THROUGH
20 YEARS OF HELL.

02:53.844 --> 02:57.638
ALL I WANT'S A QUIET LIFE
WHERE I DRIFT AROUND,

02:57.638 --> 03:00.761
CATCH UP WITH MY...
VERY PROTECTIVE DAUGHTER.

03:00.761 --> 03:02.182
AND THAT'S
WHAT I WANT, TOO,

03:02.182 --> 03:04.144
BUT, DAD, WE HAVE TO
LOOK OUT FOR EACH OTHER.

03:04.144 --> 03:09.109
OKAY. FROM HERE ON OUT,
NO SECRETS.

03:09.109 --> 03:12.733
INCLUDING WHO I'M DATING
AND WHO YOU ARE.

03:12.733 --> 03:14.695
Jack: DAVID, THAT ALTERNATOR
IS IN WORSE SHAPE

03:14.695 --> 03:16.657
THAN WE THOUGHT.

03:18.319 --> 03:20.451
OH, YEAH, WELL, OF COURSE IT IS.
I'LL SEE TO IT.

03:20.451 --> 03:21.912
ALL RIGHT,
JUST DON'T REMOVE IT.

03:21.912 --> 03:23.033
[ Chuckling ] I THINK
IT'S HOLDING THE HULL TOGETHER.

03:25.996 --> 03:27.167
I LIKE THE SCRUFF.

03:27.167 --> 03:28.999
[ SIGHS ]

03:28.999 --> 03:31.252
ONE OF THE PERKS
OF EARLY RETIREMENT?

03:37.758 --> 03:41.181
MY DAD MENTION THIS
TO YOU?

03:41.181 --> 03:42.263
LET ME GUESS --
YOU DON'T APPROVE.

03:42.263 --> 03:44.935
HE BARELY KNOWS HER.

03:44.935 --> 03:47.017
I THOUGHT
THAT'S WHAT DATING WAS FOR,

03:47.017 --> 03:48.519
TO GET TO KNOW SOMEONE.

03:48.519 --> 03:50.351
ISN'T THAT
WHY YOU'RE WITH BEN?

03:50.351 --> 03:53.774
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

03:53.774 --> 03:56.947
GOD, JACK, I DON'T WANT THINGS
TO BE LIKE THIS BETWEEN US.

03:56.947 --> 03:59.119
[ SIGHS ]
HOW SHOULD THEY BE, EMILY?

03:59.119 --> 04:00.781
[ THUD ]
 David: JACK!

04:00.781 --> 04:01.822
JACK.
 [ SIGHS ]
 [ CLATTER ]

04:01.822 --> 04:03.784
HE DIDN'T LISTEN
TO A WORD I SAID.

04:03.784 --> 04:05.205
BETTER GET DOWN THERE.
 NEED YOUR HELP!

04:05.205 --> 04:06.787
HEY, JACK.
 OW.

04:06.787 --> 04:09.370
IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU
BACK ON A BOAT.

04:09.370 --> 04:11.372
[ STEAM HISSING ]

04:19.009 --> 04:22.643
OH, MY GOD! YES!

04:22.643 --> 04:24.014
OH, DON'T STOP.

04:24.014 --> 04:26.437
THIS IS AMAZING, NOLAN!
 [ CHUCKLES ]

04:26.437 --> 04:29.059
EASY, TIGER --
SAVE SOME OF THAT ROAR

04:29.059 --> 04:30.851
FOR WHEN THEY BREAK OUT
THE HOT STONES.

04:30.851 --> 04:31.982
AHH!

04:31.982 --> 04:34.985
SO THIS IS WHAT IT'S LIKE
TO BE MARRIED.

04:34.985 --> 04:37.528
OH, I BOOKED US
A COUPLES' COOKING CLASS.

04:37.528 --> 04:39.159
OH, FUN!

04:39.159 --> 04:41.952
MM-HMM.
 AWW.

04:41.952 --> 04:45.115
I REMEMBER WHEN I WAS LITTLE
AND OUR MAID TAUGHT LYMAN AND I

04:45.115 --> 04:47.117
HOW TO MAKE BREAD PUDDIN'
WITH BOURBON SAUCE.

04:47.117 --> 04:48.369
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:48.369 --> 04:51.171
LYMAN ALWAYS HAD TO BE IN CHARGE
OF THE BOURBON.

04:51.171 --> 04:53.253
MM, SPEAKING
OF THE DEVIL'S ADVOCATE,

04:53.253 --> 04:56.046
I HEARD SOMETHING
ABOUT HIM WORKING FOR VICTORIA?

04:56.046 --> 04:57.878
YEAH.
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

04:57.878 --> 05:01.261
LYMAN'S ALWAYS BEEN DRAWN
TO STRONG WOMEN.

05:01.261 --> 05:04.425
SOUNDS MORE LIKE A MOTH
DRAWN TO A MONEY FLAME.

05:04.425 --> 05:09.730
OH, YOU KNOW...
LYMAN HAS SOME GOOD IN HIM.

05:09.730 --> 05:13.894
HE JUST KEEPS IT HIDDEN AWAY
LIKE A SQUIRREL WITH HIS ACORNS.

05:13.894 --> 05:15.065
MM, I GET IT.

05:15.065 --> 05:17.898
I'VE...GOT A SISTER
FROM ANOTHER MISTER IN EMS.

05:17.898 --> 05:19.279
AND...
[ CHUCKLES ]

05:19.279 --> 05:22.112
...SHE'S DONE
ALL SORTS OF CRAZY.

05:22.112 --> 05:23.203
AND I STILL LOVE HER.

05:23.203 --> 05:26.367
EVEN IF YOU DON'T LOVE
HER CHOICE IN BEAUS THESE DAYS?

05:28.118 --> 05:30.501
WHAT? YOU THOUGHT
YOU WERE HIDING THAT?

05:30.501 --> 05:33.083
[ CHUCKLES ]
WHAT'S WRONG WITH BEN?

05:33.083 --> 05:34.715
NOTHING.

05:34.715 --> 05:38.008
IT'S JUST...
WHEN EMILY MOVED ON,

05:38.008 --> 05:41.552
I THOUGHT
SHE'D BE MOVING TOWARDS JACK.

05:41.552 --> 05:43.884
HMM.
 I THINK HE DID, TOO.

05:43.884 --> 05:46.677
GOD,
JACK MUST BE BROKEN UP.

05:46.677 --> 05:48.058
YEAH, I DON'T KNOW.

05:48.058 --> 05:49.640
I MEAN, I SAW HIM BARTENDING
AT McGINTY'S THE OTHER NIGHT,

05:49.640 --> 05:51.231
AND HE WAS ALL SMILES.

05:51.231 --> 05:53.103
McGINTY'S?
 MM-HMM.

05:53.103 --> 05:55.105
WHEN I OFFERED HIM A JOB
 AT THE CLUB,

05:55.105 --> 05:58.108
HE TURNED ME DOWN FLAT.

05:58.108 --> 05:59.029
I THOUGHT
THAT WAS BECAUSE HE WAS --

05:59.029 --> 06:02.943
REELING FROM HEARTBREAK?
[ Chuckling ] OH, HONEY.

06:02.943 --> 06:05.536
I KNOW HOW MUCH
YOU HATE BEING WRONG,

06:05.536 --> 06:08.328
BUT TRUST YOUR FRIENDS.

06:08.328 --> 06:13.754
IF EMILY LIKES THE WAY THIS
"BIG BEN" TURNS HER CLOCK --

06:13.754 --> 06:15.996
I DON'T KNOW --
HE MAY BE WORTH HER TIME.

06:15.996 --> 06:18.048
HMM.

06:18.048 --> 06:19.920
Margaux: YOU DON'T BELIEVE
I'VE LOCATED HER?

06:19.920 --> 06:23.093
YEAH, WELL, ALL I'VE SEEN SO FAR
IS A PICTURE OF MY EX-WIFE

06:23.093 --> 06:24.965
THAT COULD HAVE BEEN
PHOTOSHOPPED FROM 10 YEARS AGO.

06:29.139 --> 06:32.012
BELIEVE ME NOW?

06:32.012 --> 06:35.936
APRIL IS AN INNOCENT
IN YOUR WAR WITH EMILY.

06:35.936 --> 06:37.478
YES, BUT YOU ARE NOT.

06:37.478 --> 06:40.360
LET ME EXPLAIN SOMETHING
ABOUT YOUR NEW GIRLFRIEND --

06:40.360 --> 06:43.023
WHEREVER SHE GOES,
SHE LEAVES PAIN IN HER WAKE,

06:43.023 --> 06:45.616
AND I KNOW YOU DON'T WANT APRIL
TO FALL VICTIM TO THAT,

06:45.616 --> 06:47.828
OR YOU WOULDN'T BE HERE.

06:47.828 --> 06:49.950
SO, DID YOU BRING
WHAT I ASKED FOR?

07:00.250 --> 07:02.042
WHY GO TO THESE LENGTHS
WHEN ANYONE WHO CARES

07:02.042 --> 07:04.044
ALREADY KNOWS THAT EMILY THORNE
IS AMANDA CLARKE?

07:04.044 --> 07:05.095
OH,
YOU MEAN THE FRIENDS

07:05.095 --> 07:07.548
WHO PERPETUATE HER LIES
AND COVER-UPS?

07:09.009 --> 07:11.852
THE WORLD OUT THERE
LIKES NOTHING MORE

07:11.852 --> 07:15.225
THAN TO DESTROY DEVILS WHO
PRETEND TO BE RIGHTEOUS ANGELS.

07:15.225 --> 07:19.359
WHEN THEY HEAR THE WHOLE STORY,
SHE WILL BE CRUCIFIED.

07:28.238 --> 07:30.030
WELL DONE,
OFFICER HUNTER.

07:44.044 --> 07:45.085
Nolan: MARGAUX FELL
RIGHT INTO OUR TRAP.

07:45.085 --> 07:46.717
BEN'S GLASSES
GOT THE FOOTAGE.

07:46.717 --> 07:49.009
BOTTLE OF RED,
NO VISIBLE LABEL.

07:49.009 --> 07:50.801
BOTTLE OF WHITE --
TRY THAT.

07:50.801 --> 07:52.683
WHERE THE HELL
IS THIS DINER?

07:52.683 --> 07:55.475
ONE BOTTLE OF PINOT GRIS
ENHANCED FOR YOUR BENEFIT.

07:55.475 --> 07:57.147
[ BEEPING ]

08:01.151 --> 08:03.193
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:05.025 --> 08:06.697
WOW.
THAT'S INCREDIBLE.

08:06.697 --> 08:09.159
TRY NOT TO DROOL
ON THE HOLOGRAM.

08:09.159 --> 08:10.450
YOU GET LOST?

08:10.450 --> 08:12.032
YEAH, WELL,
FEEDING YOUR LIES TO MARGAUX

08:12.032 --> 08:13.574
TOOK A LITTLE BIT LONGER
THAN EXPECTED.

08:13.574 --> 08:14.995
MM, BETRAYAL --

08:14.995 --> 08:17.167
YOU ALWAYS GOT TO GIVE YOURSELF
AN EXTRA 15 MINUTES.

08:17.167 --> 08:20.210
SHE DIDN'T SUSPECT
A THING.

08:20.210 --> 08:21.582
YOUR "GET SMART" SHADES.

08:21.582 --> 08:24.084
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
THEY'RE CALLED NolBans.

08:24.084 --> 08:26.256
THAT DINER CARRIES
SOME UNUSUAL BOTTLES OF WINE.

08:26.256 --> 08:29.970
YEAH. WOW, THIS ONE'S
FROM THE KEUKA WINE TRAIL.

08:29.970 --> 08:31.051
MOST OF THESE
SMALL WINERIES

08:31.051 --> 08:32.432
DON'T DISTRIBUTE
OUTSIDE THE REGION,

08:32.432 --> 08:35.015
SO I JUST CROSS-REFERENCE
THE VINEYARD WITH LOCAL DINERS

08:35.015 --> 08:37.057
THAT HAVE
A BEER-AND-WINE LICENSE.

08:37.057 --> 08:38.849
[ BEEPING, WHIRRING ]

08:38.849 --> 08:43.854
VOILà -- THE EX-WIFE
FORMERLY KNOWN AS APRIL.

08:43.854 --> 08:46.026
[ SIGHS ]
LOOK, MARGAUX'S NO AMATEUR.

08:46.026 --> 08:48.649
WE HAVE 10, MAYBE 12 HOURS
BEFORE SHE FIGURES OUT

08:48.649 --> 08:50.360
THE BIRTH CERTIFICATE'S
A FAKE.

08:50.360 --> 08:51.411
YEAH,
AND WHEN SHE DOES,

08:51.411 --> 08:54.074
SHE TELLS THIS GUY
WHERE APRIL IS.

08:54.074 --> 08:57.457
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]
 EW. WES PERKINS.

08:59.209 --> 09:01.041
THIS IS THE CHUMP
SHE LEFT YOU FOR?

09:01.041 --> 09:03.874
WELL, TO BE CLEAR,
SHE DIDN'T LEAVE ME FOR HIM.

09:03.874 --> 09:06.086
SHE LEFT ME AND THEN
HOOKED UP WITH HIM A YEAR LATER.

09:06.086 --> 09:07.257
BUT BY THE TIME
SHE LEARNED

09:07.257 --> 09:09.259
HE HAD DONE TIME
FOR AGGRAVATED ASSAULT,

09:09.259 --> 09:12.092
SHE WAS TOO AFRAID TO GET OUT,
SO SHE RAN.

09:12.092 --> 09:14.474
[ SIGHS ] WHICH IS EXACTLY WHY
WE NEED TO GET TO HER FIRST.

09:14.474 --> 09:17.137
LOOK, I STILL THINK
I SHOULD COME WITH YOU.

09:17.137 --> 09:19.179
NO. NO, I NEED TO DO THIS
ON MY OWN.

09:22.062 --> 09:24.024
[ DOOR OPENS ]

09:24.024 --> 09:26.817
SINCE WHEN DO YOU TAKE NO
FOR AN ANSWER?

09:26.817 --> 09:29.149
WHEN IT'S NOT MY MISSION,
NOLAN.

09:29.149 --> 09:30.070
WHEN HAVE
WE EVER BENEFITED

09:30.070 --> 09:32.362
BY LETTING SOMEONE ELSE
HANDLE THINGS, HMM?

09:32.362 --> 09:37.998
AND...
IF BEN HAS SECRETS,

09:37.998 --> 09:41.581
ISN'T IT BETTER TO KNOW
WHAT THEY ARE SOONER

09:41.581 --> 09:43.794
AS OPPOSED
TO WHEN IT'S TOO LATE?

09:48.048 --> 09:52.052
WHY WOULD NATALIE WATERS
THROW SUCH AN EXTRAVAGANT EVENT?

09:52.052 --> 09:53.053
TO MAKE MY LIFE HELL

09:53.053 --> 09:55.475
AND TO ANNOUNCE HER ARRIVAL
AS A ONE-PERCENTER.

09:55.475 --> 09:57.387
WELL, SHE ALREADY DID
THE FORMER,

09:57.387 --> 09:59.269
AND THE LATTER
SEEMS UNNECESSARY,

09:59.269 --> 10:02.272
CONSIDERING
HER RECENT ACQUISITION.

10:02.272 --> 10:04.645
SHE PURCHASED AN ESTATE
IN MALIBU,

10:04.645 --> 10:06.356
WHICH MAY WORK
IN YOUR FAVOR.

10:06.356 --> 10:09.529
YOU COULD BE RID OF YOUR ENEMY
AND YOUR EX

10:09.529 --> 10:11.031
IN ONE FELL SWOOP.

10:11.031 --> 10:13.613
DAVID HAS HIS DAUGHTER
AND HIS BELOVED BEACH HOUSE.

10:13.613 --> 10:15.996
HE'S NOT
GOING ANYWHERE.

10:15.996 --> 10:20.450
BUT IF SHE'S LEAVING,
WHAT IS IT SHE WANTS FROM HIM?

10:20.450 --> 10:23.453
THE ONLY PERSON
WHO'S WORTH ANYTHING IS EMILY.

10:23.453 --> 10:26.006
WELL, YOU ASK ME,
SHE'S WORTHLESS --

10:26.006 --> 10:28.458
AS, IT TURNS OUT,
ARE HER FRIENDS.

10:28.458 --> 10:32.172
SO I WILL TAKE HER DOWN
AND THOSE WHO ENABLE HER.

10:32.172 --> 10:35.175
I KNOW YOU THINK
I'M TOO EMOTIONAL, BUT...

10:35.175 --> 10:38.598
IT'S IRRELEVANT.
YOU'RE LIKE ME, MARGAUX.

10:38.598 --> 10:40.060
ONCE YOU HAVE A TARGET,

10:40.060 --> 10:42.182
YOU WILL NOT REST
UNTIL YOU HIT IT.

10:45.395 --> 10:48.358
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

10:52.442 --> 10:54.775
Jack: HEY, GUYS.

10:54.775 --> 10:56.156
Carl: DADA.
[ LAUGHS ]

10:56.156 --> 10:57.447
[ Chuckling ]
HEY, BUDDY.

10:57.447 --> 11:00.200
Phoebe: CARL'S BEEN ASKING
FOR YOU ALL DAY.

11:00.200 --> 11:01.411
AWW, SOMEONE'S HAPPY
YOU'RE HERE.

11:01.411 --> 11:02.833
YEAH, YOU MUST BE, TOO.
 [ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]

11:02.833 --> 11:04.044
[ SNIFFS ]

11:04.044 --> 11:06.126
GOT ANY, UH, BIG WEEKEND PLANS
FOR THE 4th?

11:06.126 --> 11:10.290
AND IF SO, IS IT ANYTHING
THAT CAN BE CHANGED?

11:10.290 --> 11:12.502
[ SIGHS ]
IT'S McGINTY'S.

11:12.502 --> 11:14.554
THEY --
THEY WANT ME NOW.

11:14.554 --> 11:16.676
IF I -- IF I MISS ANOTHER SHIFT,
I'M DONE THERE.

11:16.676 --> 11:19.219
YEAH, NO -- NO PROBLEM, JACK.
I COMPLETELY UNDERSTAND.

11:20.721 --> 11:24.725
HEY, I GOT TO GO, OKAY?
I GOT TO GO, ALL RIGHT?

11:24.725 --> 11:26.226
OKAY.

11:28.068 --> 11:30.070
THANK YOU.
 YEAH.

11:30.070 --> 11:31.071
HI.

11:31.071 --> 11:32.652
[ CARL CRYING ]

11:32.652 --> 11:34.444
IT'S OKAY, CARL.

11:34.444 --> 11:36.076
COME ON.
LET'S GO TO THE SWINGS.

11:36.076 --> 11:37.868
[ CRYING ]
 OH.

11:37.868 --> 11:39.990
SHH, SHH, SHH, SHH.

11:39.990 --> 11:42.322
IT'S OKAY. IT'S OKAY.
YOU'RE OKAY, HON.

11:42.322 --> 11:44.324
SHH, SHH, SHH, SHH,
SHH, SHH.

11:44.324 --> 11:46.166
[ BABBLING ]

11:46.166 --> 11:49.129
I KNOW, BABY.

11:49.129 --> 11:51.752
LYMAN.

11:51.752 --> 11:53.543
DID SOMEONE DIE?

11:53.543 --> 11:57.297
OH, C-C-CAN'T A BIG BROTHER
JUST POP BY TO SAY HEY?

11:57.297 --> 12:00.430
IN MOST FAMILIES, MAYBE,
BUT THE WAY YOU'VE TREATED ME,

12:00.430 --> 12:02.722
I TRUST YOU
AS FAR AS I CAN THROW YOU.

12:02.722 --> 12:04.805
AND WE BOTH KNOW
I INHERITED

12:04.805 --> 12:06.767
FEEBLE AUNT FAYE'S
UPPER-BODY STRENGTH.

12:06.767 --> 12:08.728
SO WHY ARE YOU HERE?

12:08.728 --> 12:10.060
WE'RE NOT KIDS ANYMORE,
LYMAN.

12:10.060 --> 12:11.812
WE DON'T HAVE TO PRETEND
TO LIKE EACH OTHER.

12:11.812 --> 12:15.235
I'VE...I'VE BEEN DOING
SOME SOUL-SEARCHING...

12:17.117 --> 12:18.528
...AND I SCREWED UP.

12:18.528 --> 12:23.283
I'VE CUT SO MANY TIES,
I FEEL LIKE I MIGHT FLOAT AWAY.

12:23.283 --> 12:26.326
YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
I FEEL CONNECTED TO ANYMORE.

12:26.326 --> 12:28.168
LYMAN --

12:28.168 --> 12:30.500
AND I'VE SPENT
ALL THESE MANY MONTHS

12:30.500 --> 12:33.043
MAKING SPEECHES
TO PEOPLE I DON'T KNOW,

12:33.043 --> 12:35.085
TRYING TO GET
THEIR SUPPORT,

12:35.085 --> 12:37.377
AND NOW I REALIZE
THAT MY JOURNEY ALL THIS TIME

12:37.377 --> 12:39.179
HAS BEEN TO GET ME TO LOOK
INTO THE EYES OF THE ONE PERSON

12:39.179 --> 12:41.551
WHOSE SUPPORT
I CAN'T DO WITHOUT.

12:41.551 --> 12:44.144
I NEVER PRETENDED
TO LIKE YOU, LOU.

12:44.144 --> 12:46.266
I NEVER HAD TO.

12:48.268 --> 12:50.690
[ SIGHS ]
COME ON.

12:56.316 --> 12:58.819
I ASKED FOR NAVY-BLUE NAPKINS,
NOT MIDNIGHT-BLUE.

12:58.819 --> 13:00.610
HAS THE SILVER
BEEN POLISHED?

13:00.610 --> 13:02.242
WHERE ARE THE REST
OF THE FLORALS?

13:02.242 --> 13:04.614
WELL, DON'T JUST STAND THERE.
MOVE.

13:04.614 --> 13:06.076
YES, MA'AM.
 OKAY, I'M ON IT.

13:06.076 --> 13:07.707
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

13:07.707 --> 13:09.079
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:09.079 --> 13:11.121
[ FOG HORN BLOWS IN DISTANCE ]

13:14.875 --> 13:17.257
INTERVIEWING
FOR A CATERING JOB?

13:17.257 --> 13:19.719
CONSIDERING HOW YOU SERVED ME
PAPERS THE OTHER DAY,

13:19.719 --> 13:24.134
I THINK YOU'D BE PERFECT
TO SPOON OUT THE HACKLEBACK.

13:24.134 --> 13:25.425
THAT'S CAVIAR, DEAR.

13:25.425 --> 13:27.427
OH, I KNOW YOU'RE TRYING
TO GET A RISE OUT OF ME,

13:27.427 --> 13:29.189
BUT I'M HERE TO MAKE AMENDS,
NATALIE.

13:29.189 --> 13:30.310
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

13:30.310 --> 13:33.273
I SEE NO REASON
WHY WE CAN'T BE CIVIL.

13:33.273 --> 13:35.105
SO TRUE.

13:35.105 --> 13:38.068
I WAS JUST SAYING THE SAME THING
TO YOUR FORMER PARAMOUR

13:38.068 --> 13:39.699
OVER DRINKS
THE OTHER NIGHT.

13:39.699 --> 13:42.242
HMM. HE IS
SUCH SPARKLING COMPANY.

13:42.242 --> 13:44.654
OH, BUT I IMAGINE THAT SPARKLE
WILL TURN TO HEARTACHE

13:44.654 --> 13:47.447
ONCE YOU LEAVE TOWN --
POSSIBLY FOR POINTS WEST?

13:47.447 --> 13:49.870
NOW, WHEREVER
WOULD YOU GET THAT IDEA?

13:49.870 --> 13:51.121
[ CHUCKLES ]

13:51.121 --> 13:53.914
I'M THINKING OF PUTTING DOWN
ROOTS RIGHT HERE --

13:53.914 --> 13:55.876
MAYBE EVEN WITH DAVID.

13:55.876 --> 13:58.458
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]
HE'S MAKING ME DINNER TONIGHT,

13:58.458 --> 14:01.131
AND I DO LOVE A MAN WHO KNOWS
HIS WAY AROUND THE KITCHEN.

14:01.131 --> 14:04.134
GOOD INDICATION
OF ALL SORTS OF TALENTS.

14:04.134 --> 14:06.927
NOW,
IF YOU'LL EXCUSE ME...

14:06.927 --> 14:11.681
HIRING OFFICE IS JUST BEYOND
THE TENNIS COURTS.

14:30.450 --> 14:32.372
[ ENGINE SHUTS OFF ]

14:34.124 --> 14:36.496
EMILY, WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING OUT HERE?

14:36.496 --> 14:37.757
I'M COMING WITH YOU.

14:37.757 --> 14:39.169
LOOK, I REALIZE
THAT YOU WANT TO HELP.

14:39.169 --> 14:40.340
BUT IF YOU CAN'T TRUST ME,
THEN I'M --

14:40.340 --> 14:42.052
WHAT MARGAUX HAS SET IN MOTION
IS NOT TO BE TAKEN LIGHTLY.

14:42.052 --> 14:44.384
PEOPLE WILL GET HURT.

14:44.384 --> 14:45.715
I'M NOT
TAKING IT LIGHTLY.

14:45.715 --> 14:47.097
LOOK, I'M SURE THERE ARE
A LOT OF THINGS

14:47.097 --> 14:49.179
THAT YOU DO BETTER THAN ME,
BUT THIS --

14:49.179 --> 14:51.811
THIS ONE THING, THIS TWISTED
CHESS GAME WITH REAL STAKES,

14:51.811 --> 14:53.393
I AM BETTER AT
THAN YOU.

14:53.393 --> 14:56.226
[ SIGHS ]
I'M COMING.

14:58.568 --> 15:01.281
[ SIGHS ]

15:04.985 --> 15:07.027
James:
THAT SHOULD DO THE TRICK.

15:07.027 --> 15:09.990
STORY IS AIRTIGHT.

15:09.990 --> 15:11.952
[ CELLPHONE CHIMES ]

15:11.952 --> 15:13.743
[ SIREN WAILS IN DISTANCE ]

15:13.743 --> 15:16.126
THE BIRTH CERTIFICATE'S
A FAKE.

15:16.126 --> 15:18.128
[ SPEAKS FRENCH ]

15:20.210 --> 15:21.211
[ SIGHS ]

15:21.211 --> 15:23.003
YOU ALWAYS KNEW
THERE WAS A CHANCE.

15:23.003 --> 15:25.425
I ASSUMED COMMON SENSE
WOULD PREVAIL.

15:25.425 --> 15:27.047
WHAT IS IT
ABOUT THAT GIRL

15:27.047 --> 15:31.101
THAT MAKES PEOPLE ACT AGAINST
THEIR OWN BEST INTERESTS?

15:39.019 --> 15:42.022
GET IN TOUCH WITH HIM.

15:42.022 --> 15:44.324
REVEAL THE LOCATION
OF THE WOMAN.

15:45.775 --> 15:48.158
I DON'T MAKE
EMPTY THREATS.

15:52.242 --> 15:54.034
[ THUNDER CRASHES ]

15:54.034 --> 15:55.996
SO, WHAT HAPPENED?

15:55.996 --> 16:00.460
I MEAN...WITH APRIL?
HOW DID IT END?

16:00.460 --> 16:04.214
I WOKE UP ONE MORNING,
AND SHE WAS PACKING A SUITCASE.

16:04.214 --> 16:07.347
JUST LIKE THAT?
NO EXPLANATION?

16:07.347 --> 16:09.679
WELL, SHE SAID
WE DIDN'T MAKE A GOOD TEAM.

16:11.511 --> 16:13.643
APPARENTLY,
I DIDN'T SURPRISE HER ENOUGH.

16:13.643 --> 16:16.976
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]
LAME.

16:16.976 --> 16:19.059
ANYWAY, THE NEXT GUY SHE MET
DID NOT HAVE THAT PROBLEM.

16:19.059 --> 16:20.650
OF COURSE, IN HIS CASE,

16:20.650 --> 16:22.402
SHE LEARNED THAT SURPRISING
ALSO MEANT DANGEROUS.

16:22.402 --> 16:25.525
WHICH IS WHEN
SHE CAME TO ME FOR HELP.

16:25.525 --> 16:28.108
MUST HAVE BEEN TOUGH
FOR YOU.

16:28.108 --> 16:30.320
NAH.
IT WASN'T, ACTUALLY.

16:30.320 --> 16:32.742
I...I DON'T KNOW.

16:32.742 --> 16:36.206
I-I HATED HER
FOR WHAT SHE DID TO ME,

16:36.206 --> 16:40.040
BUT, YOU KNOW, IT DIDN'T REPLACE
THOSE OTHER FEELINGS.

16:40.040 --> 16:42.672
YOU KNOW, THEY --
THEY NEVER WENT AWAY.

16:42.672 --> 16:44.294
IT'S WEIRD, RIGHT?

16:44.294 --> 16:45.715
NO, I GET IT.

16:45.715 --> 16:49.049
AIDEN AND I FOUGHT
AS MUCH AS WE MADE UP.

16:49.049 --> 16:51.931
[ CHUCKLES ]
WHEN I LOST HIM, I...

16:51.931 --> 16:53.303
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

16:53.303 --> 16:55.135
...FELT LIKE
I LOST EVERYTHING.

16:55.135 --> 16:57.137
YEAH.

16:57.137 --> 17:01.141
HOW DO YOU COME BACK
FROM SOMETHING LIKE THAT?

17:01.141 --> 17:03.483
I DON'T KNOW
IF YOU EVER DO.

17:13.282 --> 17:15.954
THANK YOU AGAIN
FOR DINNER.

17:15.954 --> 17:18.958
WELL, THANK YOU
FOR PRETENDING TO LIKE IT.

17:18.958 --> 17:20.119
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:20.119 --> 17:22.162
I SWEAR,
I THINK MY MEATLOAF

17:22.162 --> 17:24.214
USED TO BE MORE MEAT
AND LESS LOAF.

17:24.214 --> 17:25.464
[ LAUGHS ]

17:25.464 --> 17:27.837
AND YOU HAVE ALL THE TIME
IN THE WORLD TO GET IT RIGHT.

17:27.837 --> 17:32.382
AND ONCE THIS INDEPENDENCE DAY
SOIREE IS OVER, I'LL HELP.

17:32.382 --> 17:33.843
YEAH,
ABOUT THE SOIREE --

17:33.843 --> 17:35.725
LISTEN, THESE TYPES OF PARTIES
ARE NOT REALLY MY THING, SO I --

17:35.725 --> 17:37.137
OH, NO, NO.

17:37.137 --> 17:40.019
[ Chuckling ] NO, NO, NO,
YOU HAVE TO COME.

17:40.019 --> 17:42.602
LOOK, THEY'RE NOT
MY THING EITHER,

17:42.602 --> 17:44.984
BUT AS [SIGHS]
SILLY AS IT SOUNDS,

17:44.984 --> 17:47.777
IT'S WHAT TEDDY WANTED
FOR ME.

17:47.777 --> 17:49.529
[ SIGHS ]

17:49.529 --> 17:50.990
PLEASE?

17:54.194 --> 17:57.617
BESIDES...YOU KNOW
WHAT THE BEST PART

17:57.617 --> 18:01.121
ABOUT PICKING A GIRL UP
FOR A PARTY IS, DON'T YOU?

18:01.121 --> 18:02.792
YOU GET TO BE THE ONE
TO BRING HER HOME.

18:02.792 --> 18:03.793
[ CHUCKLES ]

18:13.012 --> 18:15.175
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

18:23.393 --> 18:26.816
DON'T WORRY. I DON'T EXPECT YOU
TO ROLL OUT THE WELCOME MAT.

18:26.816 --> 18:28.988
NO, YOU SHOULDN'T
EXPECT ANYTHING FROM ME.

18:28.988 --> 18:30.400
NATALIE WATERS IS
USING YOU.

18:30.400 --> 18:32.192
WHICH TRANSLATED MEANS
YOU'RE AFRAID

18:32.192 --> 18:34.864
THAT YOU'RE NOT GONNA SEE
ANY OF EDWARD'S MONEY

18:34.864 --> 18:36.696
AND YOU WANT ME TO HELP
TRY TO GET IT BACK.

18:36.696 --> 18:38.698
[ SIGHS ]

18:38.698 --> 18:41.661
I KNOW THAT I'M THE LAST PERSON
YOU WANT TO LISTEN TO,

18:41.661 --> 18:43.413
AND BELIEVE ME
WHEN I TELL YOU

18:43.413 --> 18:46.005
THAT YOU ARE THE LAST PERSON
I WANT TO HELP.

18:46.005 --> 18:49.709
BUT SHE'S OUR COMMON ENEMY,
AND YOU CAN'T TRUST THAT WOMAN.

18:49.709 --> 18:51.921
THAT WOMAN LOOKED AFTER
A DYING MAN

18:51.921 --> 18:53.803
WHEN HIS FAMILY
TURNED THEIR BACK ON HIM,

18:53.803 --> 18:56.095
AT A TIME WHEN HIS SON
WAS PROVEN TO BE THE MONSTER

18:56.095 --> 18:58.057
WHICH YOU TRIED TO CONVINCE
THE WORLD I WAS.

18:58.057 --> 19:02.222
SO UNLESS THIS IS
ABOUT SOMETHING ELSE...?

19:02.222 --> 19:04.394
OH, IF YOU THINK THIS IS
BECAUSE I'M JEALOUS,

19:04.394 --> 19:07.357
THEN YOUR EGO IS AS WARPED
AS YOUR JUDGMENT.

19:07.357 --> 19:10.980
NATALIE'S LYING TO YOU.
SHE'S MOVING TO CALIFORNIA.

19:10.980 --> 19:12.482
I DON'T THINK SO.
 NO?

19:12.482 --> 19:13.903
HMM.

19:13.903 --> 19:16.276
THEN WHY DID SHE BUY AN ESTATE
ON THE PACIFIC?

19:16.276 --> 19:18.117
AS AN INVESTMENT?

19:18.117 --> 19:20.990
HOW MANY HOUSES DID YOU OWN
BEFORE KARMA CAUGHT UP WITH YOU?

19:23.413 --> 19:25.625
I WAS JUST TRYING TO WARN YOU.
THAT'S ALL.

19:30.380 --> 19:32.382
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

19:57.116 --> 20:00.870
[ BELL JINGLES ]

20:04.374 --> 20:07.747
OH, MY GOODNESS!
HE'S JUST A BUNDLE OF JOY!

20:07.747 --> 20:08.998
HE'S PUTTING ON A SHOW.

20:08.998 --> 20:10.540
[ CHUCKLES ]
 WHAT HAVE WE GOT HERE?

20:10.540 --> 20:13.092
NOLAN, I THINK
THAT'S YOUR WEDDING RING.

20:13.092 --> 20:14.504
I MUST HAVE FORGOTTEN
TO PUT IT BACK ON

20:14.504 --> 20:16.005
AFTER OUR MASSAGE.

20:16.005 --> 20:17.597
WELL, THAT THING MUST BE
THE WRONG SIZE

20:17.597 --> 20:19.138
'CAUSE IT KEEPS
FALLING OFF.

20:19.138 --> 20:20.930
OH, LET'S GO PLAY.
[ SMOOCHES ]

20:20.930 --> 20:23.102
OH, I COULD JUST
EAT HIM UP!

20:23.102 --> 20:25.805
SERIOUSLY,
PASS THE MAPLE SYRUP.

20:25.805 --> 20:27.307
[ SIGHS ]
 THERE.
DO YOU LIKE THAT ONE?

20:27.307 --> 20:30.560
IT'S LIKE YOU GUYS
HAVE BEEN MARRIED FOR 10 YEARS.

20:30.560 --> 20:32.982
OH. ARE WE
THAT BORING ALREADY?

20:32.982 --> 20:34.153
WAIT -- AND IS THAT WHY

20:34.153 --> 20:36.025
YOU KEEP TAKING
EVERYBODY'S JOB OFFER BUT MINE?

20:36.025 --> 20:39.779
OR IS THAT YOU'RE AFRAID
OF RUNNING INTO EMILY AND BEN?

20:39.779 --> 20:42.322
BECAUSE I --
 THIS HAS NOTHING TO DO
WITH HER OR BEN.

20:42.322 --> 20:45.124
WHATEVER THEY HAVE OR DON'T,
I'M NOT WORRIED ABOUT THEM.

20:45.124 --> 20:48.538
ALL RIGHT.
THEN IT IS ME.

20:48.538 --> 20:50.079
I WAS RIGHT.
 WHAT?

20:50.079 --> 20:52.131
NO, IT -- [ SIGHS ]

20:52.131 --> 20:53.673
AS IF IT WASN'T BAD ENOUGH
I PISSED OFF EVERY COP

20:53.673 --> 20:55.044
IN MY PRECINCT
BY DOING THE HONORABLE THING,

20:55.044 --> 20:56.466
NOW I'M PISSING YOU OFF,
TOO?

20:56.466 --> 20:58.678
I DON'T WANT A HANDOUT,
NOLAN.

20:58.678 --> 21:00.179
NO, I-I...
[ SIGHS ]

21:00.179 --> 21:04.223
LOOK, TABLES WERE TURNED,
WOULD YOU CONSIDER IT CHARITY

21:04.223 --> 21:06.055
OR AN OPPORTUNITY

21:06.055 --> 21:08.478
TO WORK WITH A GREAT FRIEND
AND HELP HIM OUT?

21:08.478 --> 21:10.850
I MAY HAVE A WAY
TO SWEETEN THE DEAL.

21:10.850 --> 21:13.232
NOLAN, WE'VE GOT ALL THOSE
EMPTY ROOMS AT THE CLUB.

21:13.232 --> 21:15.234
WHAT IF WE TURNED ONE
INTO A DAYCARE CENTER?

21:15.234 --> 21:17.236
AH...
 WELL, NO, ACTUALLY --

21:17.236 --> 21:19.449
ACTUALLY, PEOPLE HAVE BEEN
ASKING FOR THAT.

21:19.449 --> 21:22.402
I MEAN, I GUESS IT'S PREFERABLE
TO LEAVING THEM WITH THE HELP?

21:22.402 --> 21:24.574
THE ONLY DOWNSIDE IS
THEY'RE NEVER GONNA LEARN

21:24.574 --> 21:26.035
HOW TO MAKE BREAD PUDDIN'
WITH BOURBON SAUCE.

21:26.035 --> 21:27.997
[ CHUCKLES ]
ALL RIGHT.

21:27.997 --> 21:32.211
LISTEN, JACK...
YOU CAN WORK WHEN YOU WANT.

21:32.211 --> 21:34.544
YOU CAN BRING CARL
WITH YOU.

21:34.544 --> 21:35.755
WE WILL KEEP AN EYE
ON LOUISE

21:35.755 --> 21:37.337
AND MAKE SURE
THAT SHE DOESN'T EAT HIM.

21:37.337 --> 21:38.968
WELL...
 MAYBE.

21:38.968 --> 21:43.843
OR YOU CAN KEEP INHALING SAWDUST
OFF THE FLOOR AT McGINTY'S.

21:43.843 --> 21:46.225
COME ON, JACK.
WHAT DO YOU SAY?

21:46.225 --> 21:48.638
[ SIGHS ]

21:48.638 --> 21:53.192
WELL, I-I SAY...

21:53.192 --> 21:54.854
THAT I CAN START TONIGHT.

21:54.854 --> 21:56.736
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

21:56.736 --> 22:00.740
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYS ]

22:00.740 --> 22:04.323
♪ APPLE OF THE EARTH ♪

22:04.323 --> 22:05.745
[ DOOR OPENS ]
 [ BELL JINGLES ]

22:05.745 --> 22:08.948
♪ CLARK RETURNED ♪

22:08.948 --> 22:10.249
BEN?

22:10.249 --> 22:11.751
♪ SO WET WITH TEARS ♪

22:11.751 --> 22:13.212
HEY, APRIL.

22:13.212 --> 22:15.164
[ SIGHS ]

22:15.164 --> 22:17.006
[ DOOR OPENS ]
 [ BELL JINGLES ]

22:26.766 --> 22:28.968
HOW'S IT LOOK?

22:28.968 --> 22:30.640
LIKE YOU DIDN'T TELL ME
EVERYTHING.

22:30.640 --> 22:33.643
IF HE DID, YOU'D PROBABLY BE AS
FAR AWAY FROM HIM AS POSSIBLE.

22:33.643 --> 22:35.064
FROM WHAT I UNDERSTAND,
YOU'VE BEEN HIDING

22:35.064 --> 22:38.067
FROM AN EX-CON
NAMED WES PERKINS.

22:38.067 --> 22:40.480
WOW. WHO ELSE KNOWS?

22:40.480 --> 22:42.111
I MEAN, PLEASE TELL ME
THAT YOU'RE NOT HEADING UP

22:42.111 --> 22:43.403
THE WITNESS PROTECTION PROGRAM
OR ANYTHING.

22:43.403 --> 22:45.074
APRIL, COME ON.

22:45.074 --> 22:46.245
IT'S KIM.

22:46.245 --> 22:48.077
I HAD TO DITCH MY LIFE
THANKS TO YOU.

22:48.077 --> 22:50.079
YOU?

22:50.079 --> 22:54.163
SO WHAT? YOU TOLD HER SOME
THINGS, JUST NOT EVERYTHING?

22:54.163 --> 22:55.625
SEE, THIS IS WHY
I WANTED TO COME ALONE.

22:55.625 --> 22:57.997
LOOK, A FEW MONTHS
AFTER I TOOK UP WITH WES,

22:57.997 --> 23:01.090
I WENT TO BEN ONE NIGHT
TO TALK ABOUT HIM.

23:01.090 --> 23:03.092
YOU WENT TO THE HUSBAND
YOU LEFT

23:03.092 --> 23:05.134
FOR ADVICE ABOUT THE GUY
YOU WERE SLEEPING WITH?

23:06.426 --> 23:09.509
WE WERE BEST FRIENDS,
BEN.

23:09.509 --> 23:11.721
AND I DIDN'T COME TO YOU
FOR HELP OR FOR PROTECTION

23:11.721 --> 23:14.063
OR BECAUSE YOU WERE A COP --
YOU KNEW THAT.

23:14.063 --> 23:15.394
YOU TOLD ME HOW HE FENCED
STOLEN GOODS

23:15.394 --> 23:18.017
OUT OF A WAREHOUSE IN QUEENS
AND THAT YOU WERE SCARED.

23:18.017 --> 23:20.019
I WASN'T GONNA LET THAT STAND,
AND YOU KNEW IT.

23:20.019 --> 23:22.361
SO I CALLED IN A RAID.
 WHICH I SURE AS HELL
DIDN'T WANT.

23:22.361 --> 23:24.944
BECAUSE WHEN THE COPS
FOUND SQUAT,

23:24.944 --> 23:26.736
WES KNEW THAT I WAS THE ONE
THAT TALKED,

23:26.736 --> 23:29.118
AND HE WAS GONNA MAKE DAMN SURE
THAT THAT NEVER HAPPENED AGAIN.

23:29.118 --> 23:31.701
SO I HAD TO DISAPPEAR,
THANKS TO YOU.

23:31.701 --> 23:34.534
HE WAS TRYING
TO PROTECT YOU.

23:34.534 --> 23:36.295
I DIDN'T ASK HIM TO.

23:36.295 --> 23:37.537
BY SHOWING UP, YOU DID.

23:37.537 --> 23:40.169
[ SIGHS ] LOOK,
WE'RE RUNNING OUT OF TIME.

23:40.169 --> 23:41.751
BY NOW, WES PROBABLY KNOWS
WHERE YOU ARE,

23:41.751 --> 23:43.132
AND THAT IS MY FAULT,
NOT BEN'S.

23:44.844 --> 23:46.636
YOU TWO
ARE A PERFECT MATCH.

23:46.636 --> 23:48.217
WE NEED TO
GET YOU OUT OF HERE.

23:48.217 --> 23:52.431
YOU WALK INTO MY LIFE
AFTER 10 YEARS,

23:52.431 --> 23:54.223
TRY TO UPEND IT
ALL OVER AGAIN?

23:54.223 --> 23:56.896
I'M NOT GOING ANYWHERE.

23:58.938 --> 24:00.900
[ SIGHS ]

24:00.900 --> 24:02.111
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

24:02.111 --> 24:03.362
ABSOLUTELY NOT.

24:03.362 --> 24:05.865
YOU HATE MY DRESS?

24:05.865 --> 24:08.027
NO, THE, UH,
DRESS KILLS.

24:08.027 --> 24:10.159
ABSOLUTELY NOT
TO YOUR BROTHER STAYING WITH US.

24:10.159 --> 24:12.451
HE'S TURNED OVER
A NEW LEAF.

24:12.451 --> 24:14.874
LEAVES CHANGE,
POLITICIANS DON'T.

24:14.874 --> 24:16.375
WELL, THIS ONE HAS.

24:16.375 --> 24:18.037
[ SIGHS ]

24:18.037 --> 24:21.040
LOOK, NOLAN.
MY DADDY'S DEAD.

24:21.040 --> 24:23.082
AND IN MY EYES,
SO IS MY MAMA.

24:23.082 --> 24:25.845
SO IF LYMAN WANTS TO
RECONCILE, THEN...

24:25.845 --> 24:28.427
MAYBE I WANT THAT,
TOO.

24:31.390 --> 24:35.394
BESIDES,
I...KIND OF ALREADY SAID YES.

24:35.394 --> 24:37.687
WITHOUT ASKING ME?

24:37.687 --> 24:42.481
LOU, SEE, ALL I HAVE TRIED TO DO
IS PROTECT YOU.

24:42.481 --> 24:44.063
I MEAN, DO YOU EVEN KNOW
WHAT IT MEANS TO BE IN A --

24:44.063 --> 24:47.066
IN A MARRIAGE,
IN A PARTNERSHIP?

24:47.066 --> 24:48.568
YES, I DO.

24:48.568 --> 24:50.700
IT MEANS WE BOTH BRING
OUR BAGGAGE

24:50.700 --> 24:53.072
AND OUR ECCENTRICITIES
INTO THIS UNION,

24:53.072 --> 24:56.075
AND IT IS OUR JOB TO RESPECT
EACH OTHER'S QUIRKS --

24:56.075 --> 24:59.709
AMONG MINE,
BEING MY FAMILY.

24:59.709 --> 25:02.121
AND MINE?

25:02.121 --> 25:04.964
WELL...
[ SIGHS ]

25:04.964 --> 25:07.336
HOW ABOUT THE FACT...

25:07.336 --> 25:09.178
THAT YOU KEEP LOSING
YOUR WEDDING RING

25:09.178 --> 25:11.180
AND I FIND IT
ALL OVER THE HOUSE

25:11.180 --> 25:15.184
AND I RETURN IT BACK TO YOU
WITHOUT ONCE ASKING YOU

25:15.184 --> 25:16.556
WHY YOU KEEP
TAKING IT OFF?

25:16.556 --> 25:20.139
BECAUSE I RESPECT YOU ENOUGH
NOT TO ASK.

25:20.139 --> 25:22.141
SO WHY CAN'T YOU GIVE ME
THE SAME RESPECT?

25:22.141 --> 25:25.194
WELL, MEMORY SERVES,
YOU'VE GOT A YACHT

25:25.194 --> 25:26.986
THAT LYMAN
CAN STAY ON --

25:26.986 --> 25:29.148
WELL, UNLESS THE SEA
MAKES HIM AS SICK

25:29.148 --> 25:30.860
AS HIS PRESENCE MAKES ME.

25:35.244 --> 25:37.036
Natalie: ALMOST READY.

25:37.036 --> 25:39.078
YOU ARE
A VERY PATIENT MAN.

25:39.078 --> 25:40.660
TAKE YOUR TIME.

25:40.660 --> 25:41.661
[ CLATTER ]

25:41.661 --> 25:42.662
AW. [ SIGHS ]

25:42.662 --> 25:44.253
EVERYTHING ALL RIGHT?

25:44.253 --> 25:47.967
[ SIGHS ] DAVID.

25:47.967 --> 25:50.509
IT'S TIME YOU KNOW THE TRUTH --
I AM A KLUTZ.

25:50.509 --> 25:51.671
TRIPPED ON MY STILETTO,

25:51.671 --> 25:53.933
WENT RIGHT INTO
THE MAKEUP TABLE.

25:53.933 --> 25:56.936
TEDDY USED TO SAY
IT MADE ME ENDEARING.

25:56.936 --> 25:59.018
REALLY, ALL IT DOES IS
MAKE ME BRUISE.

25:59.018 --> 26:00.770
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]
 DO YOU NEED SOME ICE?

26:00.770 --> 26:03.522
MAYBE SOME ASPIRIN?
THERE MIGHT BE SOME IN MY PURSE.

26:08.608 --> 26:09.989
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

26:12.031 --> 26:14.033
FIND ANYTHING?

26:14.033 --> 26:15.574
UH, SURE DID.

26:15.574 --> 26:18.327
[ DOOR OPENS ]

26:19.869 --> 26:22.541
AH. THANKS.

26:22.541 --> 26:26.876
♪ OH, OH-OH-OH ♪

26:26.876 --> 26:28.467
♪ I MUST BE TOUGH ♪

26:28.467 --> 26:31.881
SHE SAID I'M THOUGHTLESS
AND CONTROLLING.

26:31.881 --> 26:33.472
YOU PUT A DAYCARE CENTER
DOWN THE HALL

26:33.472 --> 26:34.884
SO I CAN BRING MY KID
TO WORK.

26:34.884 --> 26:37.056
♪ DON'T GIVE IT UP ♪
 THAT'S NOT THOUGHTLESS.

26:37.056 --> 26:38.387
WHAT ABOUT CONTROLLING?

26:38.387 --> 26:42.021
'CAUSE NOW SHE'S MAD AT ME.
I'M MAD AT HER.

26:42.021 --> 26:43.983
THIS IS STILL
A FAKE MARRIAGE, RIGHT?

26:43.983 --> 26:46.185
UH, IT'S TRICKY.

26:46.185 --> 26:48.187
ARE YOU ATTRACTED
TO HER?

26:48.187 --> 26:50.109
JACK,
HAVE YOU SEEN HER?

26:50.109 --> 26:51.941
EVERYONE FROM SOUTHAMPTON
TO THE SOUTH POLE

26:51.941 --> 26:53.532
IS ATTRACTED --
 YES, BUT THAT DOESN'T MEAN

26:53.532 --> 26:54.784
THAT THEY SHOULD
BE MARRIED TO HER.

26:54.784 --> 26:56.365
AND THAT BRINGS ME
TO THE OTHER THING.

26:56.365 --> 26:58.658
THIS RING -- NO ONE'S ATTRACTED
TO ME WHEN I WEAR IT.

26:58.658 --> 27:01.120
LOOK, IT'S CLEAR TO ME THAT
YOU WANT TWO DIFFERENT THINGS,

27:01.120 --> 27:02.912
WHICH MEANS YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE DOING.

27:02.912 --> 27:04.874
NO. JACK, I DON'T.

27:04.874 --> 27:09.088
I MEAN, AT LEAST
THAT'S THE ONE CONSTANT IN...

27:09.088 --> 27:11.210
EVERY TWISTED RELATIONSHIP
I'VE EVER HAD.

27:11.210 --> 27:14.013
WELL,
SOMETHING TO CHEW ON.

27:14.013 --> 27:16.055
SOMETHING
TO TALK TO YOUR WIFE ABOUT.

27:16.055 --> 27:17.016
MM.

27:17.016 --> 27:19.058
BUT DO YOURSELF
A FAVOR --

27:19.058 --> 27:21.020
FIGURE IT OUT
OVER SOMETHING OTHER THAN GIN.

27:21.020 --> 27:23.142
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

27:23.142 --> 27:24.934
[ GLASSES CLINK ]

27:24.934 --> 27:26.145
[ SIGHS ]

27:26.145 --> 27:29.068
♪ OH, OH-OH-OH ♪

27:29.068 --> 27:30.649
Man: GET A PHOTO OVER HERE,
PLEASE?
 Woman: OVER HERE.

27:30.649 --> 27:32.441
MR. CLARKE, THIS WAY, PLEASE.
 JUST ONE? JUST ONE. THANK YOU.

27:32.441 --> 27:34.613
THANK YOU. OH, NATALIE, DAVID.
 A PHOTO OF THE TWO
OF YOU? THANK YOU.

27:34.613 --> 27:36.075
PHOTO, PLEASE?
 TOGETHER?

27:36.075 --> 27:38.077
UH, NATALIE, DAVID.

27:38.077 --> 27:39.538
HI.

27:39.538 --> 27:42.121
MS. WATERS, YOU'VE MANAGED TO
THROW THE PARTY OF THE SUMMER...

27:42.121 --> 27:45.124
[ CHUCKLES ]
 ...AND WITH DAVID CLARKE
ON YOUR ARM NO LESS.

27:45.124 --> 27:46.335
SO, I'LL GO FIND US
SOME DRINKS.

27:46.335 --> 27:47.336
ALL RIGHT.

27:47.336 --> 27:48.497
SO, WHAT'S IT LIKE
TO DATE HIM?

27:48.497 --> 27:50.289
UH...
[ LAUGHS ]

27:50.289 --> 27:52.251
WELL, AS WE ALL KNOW,
HE'S BEEN THROUGH A LOT.

27:52.251 --> 27:54.093
SO IT'S NOT ALL SUNSHINE
AND RAINBOWS.

27:54.093 --> 27:55.004
HMM,
HOW DO YOU MEAN?

27:55.004 --> 27:56.255
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

27:56.255 --> 28:00.099
YOU SEE FLASHES OF THIS OR THAT,
AND THERE ARE...

28:00.099 --> 28:04.353
THERE ARE MOMENTS
WHEN I HARDLY RECOGNIZE HIM.

28:04.353 --> 28:05.935
BUT THEN HE'S BACK,
AND --

28:05.935 --> 28:07.516
ARE YOU SAYING
THAT YOU'RE SCARED OF HIM?

28:07.516 --> 28:11.941
NO. GOD, NO.
NO, I WOULD NEVER SAY THAT.

28:11.941 --> 28:13.522
WHATEVER IT IS
HE'S GOING THROUGH,

28:13.522 --> 28:15.314
I'M SURE
I CAN HANDLE IT.

28:17.196 --> 28:18.988
ENJOY THE PARTY.

28:18.988 --> 28:21.580
[ CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING ]
 Man: CAN WE GET A PHOTO, PLEASE?

28:21.580 --> 28:23.743
OH, THAT'S QUITE A PORTRAIT
YOU'RE PAINTING.

28:23.743 --> 28:25.324
HMM.
 TROUBLE IN PARADISE?

28:25.324 --> 28:28.287
DON'T WORRY ABOUT ME.
I'LL BE FINE.

28:28.287 --> 28:31.290
OH, I HAVE NO DOUBT.
[ CHUCKLES ]

28:31.290 --> 28:32.711
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

28:32.711 --> 28:35.004
DANIELLE?
 Woman: THANK YOU.

28:35.004 --> 28:37.797
THANK YOU.
 WELL, LOOK, SIS,
I DON'T WANT TO BE THE CAUSE

28:37.797 --> 28:40.009
OF ANY, UH, STRIFE.

28:40.009 --> 28:41.600
I CAN FIND ANOTHER PLACE
TO LIVE.

28:41.600 --> 28:45.054
LYMAN, NO.
YOU'RE MY FAMILY.

28:45.054 --> 28:47.807
WELL, IN YOUR CASE, FAMILY
HASN'T ALWAYS BEEN SO RELIABLE.

28:47.807 --> 28:50.189
I MEAN,
NOLAN'S RIGHT ABOUT THAT.

28:50.189 --> 28:52.902
THAT'S JUST BECAUSE
HE DOESN'T KNOW YOU LIKE I DO.

28:52.902 --> 28:57.116
REMEMBER WHEN WE WERE KIDS,
HOW MUCH I LOOKED UP TO YOU?

28:57.116 --> 28:58.027
[ SCOFFS ]

28:58.027 --> 29:00.069
GOD, I USED TO
FOLLOW YOU AROUND SO MUCH

29:00.069 --> 29:01.991
IT WAS LIKE YOU HAD
A SECOND SHADOW.

29:01.991 --> 29:03.532
WELL, NOW ALL I HAVE

29:03.532 --> 29:06.786
IS YOUR HUSBAND'S EYES
ON THE BACK OF MY NECK.

29:06.786 --> 29:08.788
IT'S BEST
I RESPECT HIS WISHES.

29:08.788 --> 29:11.000
YEAH, I JUST WISH
HE'D RESPECT MINE.

29:11.000 --> 29:12.131
WELL, IT'S YOUR CALL,

29:12.131 --> 29:15.254
BUT I-I-I SAY DON'T LET YOUR
OLD FAMILY SINK YOUR NEW ONE.

29:15.254 --> 29:17.086
[ SIGHS ]

29:17.086 --> 29:19.178
SEE -- [ SIGHS ]

29:19.178 --> 29:21.720
WHY CAN'T HE JUST SEE
THIS SIDE OF YOU?

29:25.014 --> 29:27.016
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]

29:27.016 --> 29:30.439
[ ENGINE REVS ]

29:33.352 --> 29:34.563
[ TRUCK DOOR CLOSES ]

29:34.563 --> 29:38.777
[ BELL JINGLES ]

29:38.777 --> 29:41.110
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

29:41.110 --> 29:46.205
HELLO, APRIL.
BEEN A LONG TIME.

29:50.079 --> 29:52.211
THE HELL ARE YOU?

29:52.211 --> 29:55.174
THE LAST PERSON
YOU WANT TO PLAY WITH.

29:56.625 --> 29:58.878
[ BOTH GRUNTING ]

29:58.878 --> 30:00.799
[ Chuckling ] OH.

30:00.799 --> 30:02.681
[ METAL CLANGS ]

30:02.681 --> 30:05.054
[ Muffled ] OH!
LET GO OF ME.

30:05.054 --> 30:06.425
[ GRUNTS ]

30:06.425 --> 30:08.227
[ HANDCUFFS CLICKING ]
 [ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

30:08.227 --> 30:09.348
[ GRUNTING ]

30:11.190 --> 30:13.142
MAYBE SECOND TO LAST.

30:19.899 --> 30:22.151
STAY -- STAY WARM
AND STAY OUT OF TROUBLE.

30:22.151 --> 30:23.112
[ TOWEL SNAPS ]
 GOT TO GO.

30:23.112 --> 30:25.534
ALL RIGHT, NOLAN. "MONEY
WHERE YOUR MOUTH IS" TIME.

30:25.534 --> 30:27.536
I'M CLOCKING OUT,
AND I'M TAKING CARL TO BAY PARK

30:27.536 --> 30:28.657
TO SEE THE FIREWORKS.

30:28.657 --> 30:30.409
UH,
AND I INSIST YOU DO.

30:30.409 --> 30:32.541
DON'T YOU MEAN TO SAY THAT,
"I KNOW THAT WE DISCUSSED THIS,

30:32.541 --> 30:34.253
BUT I NEED YOU TO STICK AROUND
FOR ANOTHER HOUR"?

30:34.253 --> 30:36.795
ALL RIGHT, FIRST, THAT'S
A TERRIBLE IMPRESSION OF ME.

30:36.795 --> 30:38.007
[ CHUCKLES ]

30:38.007 --> 30:40.839
AND SECOND OF ALL, UH,
WE ALL HAVE CAUSE TO CELEBRATE.

30:40.839 --> 30:43.632
EMS CALLED --
TURNS OUT SHE AND BEN

30:43.632 --> 30:46.845
HAVE MANAGED TO THWART
LADY LeMARCHAL'S ATTEMPTS

30:46.845 --> 30:48.227
TO RATTLE
OUR COLLECTIVE CAGES.

30:48.227 --> 30:50.469
YES,
PUNCHES WERE THROWN.

30:50.469 --> 30:52.972
SHE TOOK BEN WITH HER?

30:52.972 --> 30:55.604
AW, JACK,
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

30:55.604 --> 30:57.186
I MEAN,
THEIR LITTLE ROAD TRIP

30:57.186 --> 30:59.979
WAS MORE...REVENGE
THAN ROMANCE.

30:59.979 --> 31:02.241
YEAH?
WHO GOT PUNCHED?

31:02.241 --> 31:04.073
[ CHUCKLES ]
KIDDING.

31:04.073 --> 31:05.244
MOSTLY.

31:05.244 --> 31:07.907
ANYWAYS, LOOK,
I HOPE THAT MARGAUX REALIZES

31:07.907 --> 31:09.909
IT'S TIME TO DROP
THIS VENDETTA.

31:09.909 --> 31:12.701
[ SIGHS ] I...
IT'S NOT HER.

31:12.701 --> 31:15.294
IT'S KIND OF
BECOMING HER.

31:15.294 --> 31:17.706
RULE OF
THE RED SHARPIE --

31:17.706 --> 31:20.089
IT'S HARD
TO PUT THAT CAP BACK ON.

31:20.089 --> 31:25.054
BUT...WELL,
THAT DOESN'T CONCERN YOU.

31:25.054 --> 31:28.217
GO CHECK OUT THE, UH,
RIGHT KIND OF FIREWORKS.

31:30.179 --> 31:33.222
ENJOYING YOURSELF,
MR. ELLIS?

31:33.222 --> 31:34.353
I AM NOW.

31:34.353 --> 31:36.355
HMM.
 AND HOW ABOUT YOU?

31:36.355 --> 31:38.978
THIS ISN'T EXACTLY
YOUR HOLIDAY.

31:38.978 --> 31:40.019
NOW,
PLEASE DON'T TELL ME

31:40.019 --> 31:41.981
YOU'VE BEEN USING MY RETAINER
FOR ONE.

31:41.981 --> 31:47.116
THE KEY
TO NOLAN ROSS' HOUSE.

31:47.116 --> 31:50.909
BABY SIS
JUST WANTS HER FAMILY.

31:50.909 --> 31:52.911
AND AS FOR MY WANTS...

31:52.911 --> 31:55.494
WELL, KUDOS FOR EARNING
YOUR SISTER'S TRUST.

31:55.494 --> 31:57.456
NOW FINISH EARNING MINE,

31:57.456 --> 32:00.339
AND YOU GET THE REST
OF YOUR FEE.

32:02.091 --> 32:06.135
NOLAN ROSS' SECRETS
ARE SOMEWHERE IN THAT HOUSE.

32:06.135 --> 32:09.048
FIND THEM.
AND THEN FIND ME.

32:09.048 --> 32:12.181
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

32:19.228 --> 32:20.859
WATCH YOUR HEAD.
 [ GRUNTS ]

32:20.859 --> 32:22.361
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

32:22.361 --> 32:25.194
[ SIGHS ]
SO, AFTER HE, UH --

32:25.194 --> 32:27.196
HE SWUNG AT ME,
I HID BEHIND THE COUNTER.

32:27.196 --> 32:29.198
I WAS SCARED FOR MY LIFE.

32:29.198 --> 32:30.739
LUCKILY,
I SAW WHAT WAS GOING ON,

32:30.739 --> 32:32.531
AND I WAS ABLE TO DISARM
AND SUBDUE THE ASSAILANT.

32:32.531 --> 32:34.243
WHAT HAPPENS NOW?

32:34.243 --> 32:36.665
WELL, THE SHEET SAYS
HE'S GOT TWO STRIKES ALREADY.

32:36.665 --> 32:38.127
SO THIS MAKES HIM
A LIFER.

32:39.038 --> 32:42.041
IT MEANS YOU'VE GOT NOTHING
TO WORRY ABOUT, MA'AM.

32:42.041 --> 32:43.252
TAKE CARE.

32:43.252 --> 32:45.254
THANK YOU.

32:48.217 --> 32:51.090
[ CAR DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

32:55.354 --> 32:57.356
[ SIGHING ]

33:00.309 --> 33:03.062
I DON'T EVEN KNOW
WHAT TO SAY.

33:03.062 --> 33:04.153
I MEAN, I DO. I DO.

33:04.153 --> 33:08.157
THANK YOU BOTH
FOR COMING TO WARN ME

33:08.157 --> 33:09.738
AND FOR NOT LEAVING
UNTIL IT GOT THROUGH.

33:09.738 --> 33:12.741
I KNOW I CAN BE...
PRETTY STUBBORN SOMETIMES.

33:12.741 --> 33:15.744
[ CHUCKLES ]
TRUST ME, I'M THE SAME.

33:15.744 --> 33:18.117
[ CHUCKLES ]
YEAH.

33:18.117 --> 33:19.168
WELL,
I GUESS HE'S GOT A TYPE.

33:21.170 --> 33:23.962
[ CHUCKLES ]

33:27.926 --> 33:30.049
[ RUBS BACK ]

33:36.515 --> 33:40.099
I'M SORRY.
I JUST HAD TO STEAL YOU AWAY.

33:40.099 --> 33:42.441
THE FIREWORKS
ARE STARTING SOON.

33:42.441 --> 33:45.444
OH, I THINK WE CAN MAKE
A MUCH BETTER SHOW.

33:45.444 --> 33:48.277
HMM?

33:48.277 --> 33:50.989
[ CHUCKLES ]

33:50.989 --> 33:53.822
[ SCOFFS ]

33:53.822 --> 33:55.154
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

33:55.154 --> 33:59.037
YOU MONSTER!
GET YOUR HANDS OFF OF ME!

33:59.037 --> 34:01.330
OH.

34:01.330 --> 34:03.001
YOU'RE SETTING ME UP.

34:03.001 --> 34:04.583
NO ONE
WILL EVER BELIEVE YOU.

34:04.583 --> 34:07.126
WHICH IS WHY I INFORMED
THE REPORTER EARLIER

34:07.126 --> 34:09.547
THAT YOU'RE
A DEEPLY DISTURBED MAN --

34:09.547 --> 34:10.879
I JUST THOUGHT
I COULD HANDLE IT.

34:12.010 --> 34:15.344
DAVID, NO!
YOU'RE HURTING ME!

34:15.344 --> 34:17.556
YOU GONNA DESTROY
CONRAD'S WATCH, TOO?

34:18.976 --> 34:22.601
"TO BUNNY, ETERNALLY YOURS --
CONRAD."

34:22.601 --> 34:24.893
I RECOGNIZED IT
IN YOUR PURSE.

34:24.893 --> 34:27.735
SEE, I HAD A SECRETARY ONCE
WHO HAD THE EXACT SAME WATCH.

34:27.735 --> 34:31.150
LYDIA DAVIS
WAS A VILE WHORE.

34:31.150 --> 34:34.322
CONRAD GRAYSON
LOVED ME.

34:34.322 --> 34:36.614
HE PROMISED ME EVERYTHING
WHEN HE DIED.

34:36.614 --> 34:39.288
YOU AREN'T THE FIRST GIRL
THAT HE SEDUCED WITH HIS ESTATE,

34:39.288 --> 34:41.699
BUT YOU MIGHT BE
THE MOST DELUDED AND AMBITIOUS.

34:41.699 --> 34:43.202
YOU DIDN'T GET
CONRAD'S MONEY,

34:43.202 --> 34:45.164
SO YOU WENT AFTER
HIS DYING FATHER?

34:45.164 --> 34:48.417
AND THE BASTARD WAS INTENT
ON LEAVING VICTORIA EVERYTHING.

34:48.417 --> 34:51.420
I STARVED HIM
UNTIL HE HAD NO CHOICE

34:51.420 --> 34:55.053
BUT TO PICK UP THE DAMN PEN
AND SIGN THE NEW WILL.

34:55.053 --> 34:57.094
SO WHY COME AFTER ME?

34:57.094 --> 35:00.139
AWW, HONEY.

35:00.139 --> 35:03.352
CONRAD ALWAYS WANTED ME
TO LIVE LIKE A GRAYSON,

35:03.352 --> 35:05.394
AND THAT'S NOT JUST
ABOUT THE MONEY.

35:05.394 --> 35:07.686
IT'S ABOUT THE POWER...

35:07.686 --> 35:12.691
THE POWER TO MAKE PEOPLE BELIEVE
ANYTHING YOU WANT.

35:12.691 --> 35:15.574
RUINING YOU WAS AMONG
HIS GREATEST ACCOMPLISHMENTS.

35:15.574 --> 35:17.196
SO YOU WANT THE WORLD
TO HATE ME.

35:17.196 --> 35:18.036
CONRAD DID.

35:18.036 --> 35:20.078
MAYBE HE'LL REST BETTER

35:20.078 --> 35:22.451
KNOWING THAT I'VE FINISHED
WHAT HE STARTED.

35:22.451 --> 35:24.503
OR ALTERNATIVELY,

35:24.503 --> 35:26.375
WHEN YOU EVENTUALLY
SEE HIM IN HELL,

35:26.375 --> 35:27.626
MAYBE YOU CAN TELL HIM
YOURSELF.

35:27.626 --> 35:30.209
VICTORIA.
GET OUT OF HERE.

35:30.209 --> 35:33.051
OH, I HAVE NOWHERE TO GO
UNTIL MONDAY'S COURT HEARING.

35:33.051 --> 35:36.425
OR...

35:36.425 --> 35:39.017
Natalie: I STARVED HIM
UNTIL HE HAD NO CHOICE...

35:39.017 --> 35:42.060
...YOU COULD SIMPLY
SIGN EVERYTHING OVER TO ME.

35:42.060 --> 35:44.473
THAT WAY, I RETAIN
MY RIGHTFUL INHERITANCE,

35:44.473 --> 35:46.475
AND YOU WON'T HAVE TO
GO TO PRISON.

35:46.475 --> 35:48.767
OH, AND, BUNNY,

35:48.767 --> 35:50.479
IF YOU'RE PLANNING
ON STAYING IN TOWN,

35:50.479 --> 35:52.651
DON'T WORRY ABOUT MONEY.

35:52.651 --> 35:55.033
I HEAR THE BEACH CLUB
IS HIRING.

36:02.040 --> 36:04.663
[ BEEPING ]

36:04.663 --> 36:08.086
MY, OH, MY, THE THINGS
THESE PEOPLE HAVE DONE,

36:08.086 --> 36:11.290
ALL IN THE NAME
OF THIS AMANDA CLARKE.

36:11.290 --> 36:14.092
CALL ME WHEN YOU GET THIS.

36:16.295 --> 36:18.347
LYMAN?

36:18.347 --> 36:20.509
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

36:20.509 --> 36:23.061
UH, L-LOUISE THIS, UH --
I-I KNOW HOW THIS LOOKS.

36:23.061 --> 36:25.434
LIKE YOU'RE STEALING INFORMATION
OFF MY HUSBAND'S COMPUTER.

36:25.434 --> 36:27.065
NO, I-I --
 I TRUSTED YOU.

36:27.065 --> 36:29.478
NO, I...
 GET OUT OF MY HOUSE.

36:29.478 --> 36:31.069
NOW, L-LOUISE,
YOU GIVE ME THAT BACK.

36:31.069 --> 36:32.441
[ GASPS ]
 LOUISE.

36:32.441 --> 36:33.942
LOUISE, GIVE ME THAT.

36:33.942 --> 36:35.864
YOU PLAYED ME
FOR A FOOL.

36:35.864 --> 36:38.447
YEAH, WELL, YOUR NEW FRIENDS
PLAYED YOU FIRST!

36:38.447 --> 36:40.239
OTHERWISE, WHY'S YOUR HUSBAND
GOT A HIDDEN COMPUTER

36:40.239 --> 36:41.660
BEHIND THE BUREAU?

36:41.660 --> 36:43.492
THESE ARE NOT GOOD PEOPLE,
LOUISE.

36:43.492 --> 36:46.955
MY PEOPLE ARE JUST FINE.
LET'S TALK ABOUT YOUR PEOPLE.

36:46.955 --> 36:49.087
HOW MUCH IS MARGAUX LeMARCHAL
PAYING YOU?

36:49.087 --> 36:51.670
HOW DO YOU KNOW ABOUT THAT?
 BECAUSE I'M NOT A FOOL!

36:51.670 --> 36:54.543
AND I HAVE A MUCH BETTER
THROWING ARM THAN AUNT FAYE.

36:54.543 --> 36:57.095
[ GASPS ]

36:57.095 --> 36:58.297
NO!

36:58.297 --> 37:00.429
[ BOTH GRUNT ]

37:00.429 --> 37:02.721
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

37:05.474 --> 37:06.765
[ GASPS ]

37:09.518 --> 37:12.150
[ THUD ]

37:21.820 --> 37:24.363
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

37:24.363 --> 37:26.745
[ ALL CHEERING ]

37:33.081 --> 37:36.875
I GUESS THIS IS TECHNICALLY
YOUR FOURTH OF JULY PARTY NOW.

37:36.875 --> 37:38.677
NOT WITH THIS DECOR.

37:38.677 --> 37:40.258
[ CHEERING CONTINUES ]

37:40.258 --> 37:42.431
WHAT WILL YOU DO WITH
ALL THE MONEY COMING YOUR WAY?

37:42.431 --> 37:45.434
I'LL USE IT TO ENSURE THAT
THE DANIEL GRAYSON FOUNDATION

37:45.434 --> 37:47.646
RESTORES MY BOY'S
GOOD NAME.

37:47.646 --> 37:49.848
IT'LL TAKE TIME.

37:49.848 --> 37:53.061
BUT I CAN SEE NO CAUSE
MORE WORTHWHILE.

37:53.061 --> 37:57.776
WELL, ON THE SUBJECT OF NAMES,
UH, I WANT TO THANK YOU

37:57.776 --> 38:00.238
FOR MAKING SURE
THAT MINE WASN'T RUINED --

38:00.238 --> 38:01.660
AGAIN.

38:01.660 --> 38:06.074
WELL...I GUESS
THERE'S A SILVER LINING

38:06.074 --> 38:07.746
TO NOT KILLING ME
AFTER ALL.

38:11.169 --> 38:13.332
Man: YEAH!

38:13.332 --> 38:16.545
[ ENGINE REVVING ]

38:16.545 --> 38:20.629
ARE YOU READY TO SEE
THE FIREWORKS, PAL, HUH?

38:20.629 --> 38:22.971
[ CHUCKLES ]
 [ SIREN WAILING ]

38:22.971 --> 38:25.974
[ SIGHS ]

38:25.974 --> 38:28.186
COME ON. SERIOUSLY?

38:42.150 --> 38:43.532
[ SIGHS ]

38:43.532 --> 38:46.705
WELL, IF IT ISN'T
FORMER OFFICER PORTER.

38:46.705 --> 38:51.119
ENJOYING YOUR FREE TIME?
MAYBE A LITTLE TOO MUCH?

38:51.119 --> 38:52.661
WHAT IS IT, SCHAEFER?

38:52.661 --> 38:55.544
WE RECEIVED A TIP THERE'S
A DRUNK DRIVER ON THE ROAD

38:55.544 --> 38:56.755
IN A TRUCK
THAT MATCHES YOURS.

38:56.755 --> 38:58.126
WELL, YOU PULLED OVER
THE WRONG ONE.

38:58.126 --> 38:59.628
I HAVEN'T HAD ANYTHING
TO DRINK ALL NIGHT.

38:59.628 --> 39:01.049
SO CAN I GO?

39:01.049 --> 39:04.012
I'M JUST TRYING TO TAKE MY KID
TO BAY PARK FOR FIREWORKS.

39:04.012 --> 39:05.514
AND I'M JUST
DOING MY JOB,

39:05.514 --> 39:08.807
OR HAVE YOU ALREADY FORGOTTEN
POLICE PROTOCOL?

39:08.807 --> 39:10.138
STEP OUT OF THE CAR.

39:15.974 --> 39:18.146
WES PERKINS WAS ARRESTED
FOR ASSAULT

39:18.146 --> 39:19.357
EARLIER THIS EVENING.

39:19.357 --> 39:21.279
HMM.

39:21.279 --> 39:22.691
NOTHING WILL BE TRACED
BACK TO YOU.

39:22.691 --> 39:23.742
[ FIREWORKS EXPLODING ]

39:23.742 --> 39:26.825
EMILY IS ONE STEP AHEAD...
ALWAYS.

39:26.825 --> 39:28.827
CAN'T SAY THE SAME
FOR THE REST OF THEM.

39:28.827 --> 39:30.789
JACK PORTER
WAS TAKEN CARE OF.

39:30.789 --> 39:31.990
GOOD.

39:31.990 --> 39:33.121
AS FOR NOLAN ROSS,

39:33.121 --> 39:35.794
I EXPECT THE CONTENTS
OF HIS WELL-PROTECTED HARD DRIVE

39:35.794 --> 39:38.086
WILL BE MORE THAN ENOUGH
TO RUIN THEM ALL.

39:38.086 --> 39:40.088
I SHOULD HAVE IT
WITHIN THE HOUR.

39:40.088 --> 39:41.920
[ SOFT MUSIC PLAYS ]

39:45.173 --> 39:48.306
HERE YOU ARE.

39:48.306 --> 39:51.720
AND I SEARCHED
THE WHOLE PARTY FOR YOU.

39:51.720 --> 39:55.103
I LEFT EARLY.

39:55.103 --> 39:57.476
NOLAN.

39:57.476 --> 39:59.067
I DID SOMETHING BAD.

39:59.067 --> 40:02.070
[ SIGHS ] NO.

40:02.070 --> 40:04.903
NO, YOU DIDN'T.

40:04.903 --> 40:06.404
I DID.

40:06.404 --> 40:11.530
LOUISE, I KNOW THIS MARRIAGE
IS UNTRADITIONAL,

40:11.530 --> 40:15.954
BUT [CHUCKLES]
SO ARE WE.

40:15.954 --> 40:18.166
AND WE STILL HAVE A LOT
TO FIGURE OUT.

40:18.166 --> 40:20.168
[ SIGHS ]

40:20.168 --> 40:22.170
BUT WHILE WE DO,
LYMAN IS...

40:22.170 --> 40:24.753
WELCOME TO STAY.

40:24.753 --> 40:27.756
MORE THAN WELCOME.

40:27.756 --> 40:30.308
[ GASPS ]

40:30.308 --> 40:34.473
I'M SO GLAD
YOU SAID THAT.

40:34.473 --> 40:36.264
BECAUSE HE'S IN THE GUEST ROOM
RIGHT NOW.

40:36.264 --> 40:38.266
HE, UH...

40:38.266 --> 40:41.109
HAD A FEW TOO MANY
AND PASSED OUT.

40:41.109 --> 40:43.151
[ CHUCKLES ]
YEAH, OF COURSE HE DID.

40:43.151 --> 40:46.154
[ SIGHS ]
IT'S BEEN A LONG DAY.

40:46.154 --> 40:48.116
TALK IN THE MORNING?
 MM-HMM.

40:48.116 --> 40:51.159
HMM.
[ SMOOCHES ]

40:53.782 --> 40:56.164
HEY.

40:56.164 --> 40:57.285
HMM?

40:57.285 --> 40:59.127
WONDER TWINS.

41:06.885 --> 41:09.047
SO, IF YOU'RE MARGAUX,
WHAT DO YOU DO NEXT?

41:09.047 --> 41:12.300
WHATEVER IT IS, SHE'S DESPERATE,
WHICH MAKES HER DANGEROUS.

41:12.300 --> 41:15.143
SHE'LL KEEP LOOKING FOR...

41:15.143 --> 41:16.685
VULNERABILITIES
AND WEAKNESSES --

41:16.685 --> 41:19.057
MINE AND MY FRIENDS.
I MEAN...

41:19.057 --> 41:20.689
[ SIGHS ]

41:20.689 --> 41:24.603
GOING AFTER YOUR FIRST LOVE
WAS RUTHLESS

41:24.603 --> 41:26.775
AND...SMART.

41:26.775 --> 41:30.448
A PERSON'S FIRST LOVE
IS THEIR WEAK SPOT.

41:30.448 --> 41:34.993
JUST LIKE DANIEL PROVED
TO BE HERS.

41:34.993 --> 41:37.916
SO, WHO'S YOURS?

41:37.916 --> 41:41.499
MY WHAT?
 YOUR WEAK SPOT.

41:41.499 --> 41:43.461
JACK.

41:43.461 --> 41:45.123
JACK?

41:45.123 --> 41:47.085
JACK, WAS YOUR FIRST LO--
 NO, BEN -- JACK.

41:47.085 --> 41:49.257
THAT'S WHAT
I'M TRYING TO FIGURE OUT.

41:49.257 --> 41:51.590
WE GOT A CALL.

41:51.590 --> 41:53.181
I'M TELLING YOU,
THERE'S SOMETHING WRONG.

41:53.181 --> 41:54.843
I, UH -- YOU KNOW ME.

41:54.843 --> 41:56.014
I WOULDN'T DRINK
AND GET BEHIND THE WHEEL.

41:56.014 --> 41:58.266
YOU BLEW .14.
AGAINST THE CAR, PORTER.

41:58.266 --> 42:01.059
TED, WE'VE GOT A KID HERE.
 [ CRYING ]

42:01.059 --> 42:03.141
NO, NO, NO!
YOU'RE NOT TAKING HIM! NO!

42:03.141 --> 42:06.444
GET YOUR HANDS OFF MY KID!
GET YOUR HANDS OFF ME!

42:06.444 --> 42:07.696
RELAX.
 [ GRUNTS ]

42:07.696 --> 42:10.528
YOU'RE NOT TAKING MY KID!
YOU'RE NOT TAKING MY KID!

42:10.528 --> 42:12.320
LET ME GO!

42:12.320 --> 42:14.953
COME ON!
COME ON! LET HIM GO!

42:14.953 --> 42:18.917
[ Crying ] LET HIM GO!
GIVE HIM TO ME! GOD, NO!

42:18.917 --> 42:20.208
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

42:20.208 --> 42:21.790
CLOSE IT UP.
